<!--
  Hardened-runtime entitlements for the aiscan Developer ID build.

  Deliberately EMPTY. A statically-linked Go binary with a Cocoa menu-bar tray
  needs no exceptions: outbound network upload is unrestricted for a
  non-sandboxed Developer ID app (network.client is an App Sandbox entitlement,
  not a hardened-runtime one), and self-update (replacing its own binary +
  re-exec) needs no entitlement either.

  Both the standalone CLI binary and the .app's main executable are signed with
  THIS file so their entitlements match — a mismatch would change the code
  identity across a self-update swap. Add an exception here (e.g.
  com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit) only if a notarization log demands it.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict/>
</plist>
